# Claude Code - Session Strategy

Best practices for efficient context management and productive sessions.

## Progressive Loading Principle

**Load only what you need, when you need it.**

### Always Load (Startup)
- Session state files (~1k tokens)
- Summary/quick files (.quick.md, README.md headers)
- Current task context only

### Load On-Demand
- Full documentation (when modifying)
- Detailed specs (when implementing)
- Historical context (when researching)

**Rule**: Reference via `@filename.md` instead of reading upfront.

## Context Budget Guidelines

| Session Type | Target | Strategy |
|--------------|--------|----------|
| Quick fix | <25% | Minimal: load only affected files |
| Feature work | <50% | Progressive: load as you go |
| Research | <60% | Selective: specific docs only |
| Architecture | <70% | Planned: /compact every 40 messages |

## Session Workflow

### Starting
1. Use existing context from previous session
2. Load task-specific files only
3. Don't read entire README/docs upfront

### Working
- Monitor context meter
- `/compact` at 70% capacity
- Use subagents for isolated tasks
- Clear between unrelated tasks

### Ending
- Save decisions to relevant docs
- Commit with descriptive messages
- Update roadmap/status files

## Key Commands

- `/compact` - Summarize and free context (use at 70%)
- `/clear` - Full reset (only when switching major tasks)
- `/context` - Check current context usage

